story.text: The [[TAKA Blog]] is generating a lot of sdaf. This appears to be connected to the fact that on all blog pages there is a section / tab at the bottom labelled "Archives", which is not functioning.

It is difficult to find out exactly where theses errors are coming from. It looks like a combination of Google trying to guess Javascript based links and some errors being generated by the blog archive functionality.
Issue: The TAKA blog is generating a lot of 404 Not Found Errors.

Nearly all of the [[Not found errors (404)]] are listed as coming from the [[TAKA Blog]] -   [https://www.google.com/webmasters/tools/crawl-errors?hl=en&authuser=0&siteUrl=http://www.himalayanacademy.com/#t2=1 Google Search Console]

As with other [[Not found errors (404)]] these don’t impact the site’s ranking in Google, and we (according to Googles advice) can safely ignore them. They can however point to something wrong with the site that needs investigating:
